<p>The name Legend is a classic brand that at one point in time dominated both Commodore scenes. 
But oddly enough never did that well on the PC.
Initially the name showed in 1993 as Legend PC, but this was a short-lived unrelated group started by <a href="">ex-INC</a> members who we think later merged into <a href="">The Dream Team</a>.
</p><p>
The real Legend showed up shortly after in early 1994.
It was founded by a few European members from the original <a href="http://www.legend64.com">Legend Commodore 64 group</a> who were trying to break into the PC scene.
</p>
