<p>
In May of 1994 there was an on going fight within <a href="groups.cfm?mode=detail&org=razor1911">Razor 1911</a> between a couple of it's leaders.
Rumour had it that Butcher, who was one of these leaders was sick of people ripping off the group's financial supply.
Others suggested it was simply a power play and a clash of egos.
Eitherway, it resulted in Butcher leaving the group and taking a number of members, suppliers and sites (including Razor's Courier and EU HQ's) with him. 
</p><p>
Westbam who was both in <a href="groups.cfm?mode=detail&org=razor1911">Razor 1911</a> (PC) and Legend (C64) joined Butcher in the split and it is probably through him that they took over the running of Legend PC from the Legend Commodore 64 guys.
Legend soon found itself made up of former Razor 1911, UK <a href="groups.cfm?mode=detail&org=trsi">TRSI</a> and Legend C64/Amiga members and became quite succesfull in it's own right.
The UK TRSI joined up after they left TRSI due to problems they had with the TRSI German leadership, or specifically the lack of.
